CZ: Yes, for example, country-wide tests are carried out with regard to risky goods and sectors.
Germany: There are no regulations at federal level.
Accordingly, the statistics compiled at the federal level do not provide information on particularly "prolific" audit areas for auditors and UST special examiners.
There were different views on the analysis of such information, the benefits and the way in which it was used.
Some financial directorates provide such information to financial institutions, but they are free to decide whether or not to use it.
4.5.4 Comparison and Evaluation
As a result, large amounts of information are processed automatically in the CZ. Data from UST audits, as well as key figures from balance sheets, profit and loss accounts are processed in the system, among other things.
The CZ is able to control the selection of high-risk cases based on a wide range of information.
The same applies to the evaluation and management of UST tests in general.
In the CZ, the establishment of a special finance office for large enterprises is planned for 2012.
In Germany, the financial administration does not collect comparable amounts of data.
Accordingly, it is more difficult to perform these tasks in the same way.
The emphasis is more on the selection of individual cases.
