5. Conclusions
The cooperation between the two courts of auditors has proved successful.
Thus, necessary knowledge could be gained on the systems applied in both countries: This applies in particular to: • intra-Community sales, • risk management in the VAT system, in particular with regard to the selection of high-risk transactions, • recovery of VAT receivables and • VAT audit of large companies.
The audit revealed differences in the strategies for detecting VAT fraud and the systems outlined above.
This knowledge can be used to improve existing procedures.
They can also be used to stimulate a discussion among interested parties about the approaches and strategies that can be used to combat fraud, such as the relationship between Member States and the European Commission.
The experience and knowledge gained should encourage the joint examination of the administration of the UST in the future.
